1
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:49,671
- Good morning, Nancy.
- Good morning.

2
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,800
Man walking.

3
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:30,000
Put your left hand on top of your head.

4
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,100
Now the other one.

5
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:54,000
In the years since
my client's incarceration...

6
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:57,300
A 12-year sentence for manslaughter
during a bank robbery.

7
00:05:57,400 --> 00:06:01,300
In the years since
Michael Bosworth's incarceration,

8
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:05,300
he's completed the Johns Hopkins
creative writing workshop.

9
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:10,300
In addition, I present the court
two letters of character reference

10
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,300
from nationally known authors.

11
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:16,900
I'll produce transcripts from the mothers
of two men he shot down in the past.

12
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:22,700
I'll also point out that Michael Bosworth's
IQ has been measured above 130.

13
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:26,800
The prosecution concedes that
Michael Bosworth is very intelligent.

14
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,500
But we also know
he always reverts to violence.

15
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,000
The charge before the court
is attempted murder.

16
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:38,300
It defies all reason that Bosworth
would jeopardise a flawless prison record

17
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,100
by attacking a guard...

18
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,900
I'm not a case history.

19
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:47,000
The defendant will speak
only when spoken to.

20
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:50,200
Bailiffs, sit this man down.

21
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:53,600
I'm just pro bono work
for her rich daddy's law firm.

22
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,100
Bailiffs, sit the man down.

23
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:59,600
I wanna go pro per.
I demand to represent myself.

24
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:02,400
My life is in jeopardy
from every guard in that prison.

25
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:09,600
And Nancy Breyers' defence is trivial,
unsuitable, weak and defeatist.

26
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:14,300
Mr Bosworth, if necessary,
I will have you gagged and bound.

27
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:18,100
Ms Breyers has represented you
diligently these past weeks.

28
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:23,300
You are fighting for your life.
You may not go pro per.

29
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:27,300
Your Honour, may I be permitted
to confer with my client in private?

30
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:31,100
I got nothing to say to you.

31
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:35,200
- Permission granted.
- I got nothing to say.

32
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,900
Man walking.

33
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,500
- I'm gonna grab a sandwich.
- You got it.

34
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,000
Stand right here.

35
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,600
Ma'am.

36
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:56,200
Hold it right there, buddy.
You stay here.

37
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:05,900
I am trying to think what more I can do
to convince you of my competence.

38
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:10,500
Please, I worked very hard to help you.

39
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:13,900
Please, I've worked very hard.

40
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:24,400
Relax, cowboy.

41
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,900
Hook him up. Hook him up.

42
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:37,500
Better do what he says.
Please put your hands behind your back.

43
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,800
Son of a bitch.

44
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:06,500
Whatever I do,
it's only because I need you.

45
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,500
- Say you need me.
- I need you.

46
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:17,100
- I want you to act scared of me.
- I am scared of you.

47
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,400
- I knew something'd go wrong.
- You got no faith.

48
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,700
Nancy. Hi. I thought you were
supposed to be in court this morning.

49
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,600
I gotta get going.

50
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:21,500
I'll wait for you...
Open your eyes and look at me!

51
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:25,100
I'll wait for you as long as it takes.

52
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,200
Nancy! Nancy!

53
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:33,900
My brother knows what he's doing.
Open the door!

54
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,600
- Where's the lawyer?
- Get outta here!

55
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,900
Nancy, are you OK?

56
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:36,500
- Daddy!
- Hey, Zack. How you doin'?

57
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,100
- OK.
- Is Mom in?

58
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:39,900
Come and see Mommy.

59
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:49,500
- Hey, Mom! It's Daddy.
- What are you doing in shorts?

60
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:52,200
It's almost winter. Go up and get changed.

61
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:57,600
You're not supposed
to be here till this afternoon.

62
00:11:58,700 --> 00:11:59,600
Hey.

63
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:04,000
I'm surprised you guys
are talking to each other.

64
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:07,500
I love your hair like that.
It's beautiful when you wear it that way.

65
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:10,600
- Come on.
- I'm late.

66
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:17,200
Mom, Kyle will be driving me
to riding class after school.

67
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:25,700
If it makes you feel better,
she's harder on me when we're alone.

68
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:28,800
Hey, come here. I want to talk to you.

69
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,700
She still going out with Kyle?

70
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Nora?

71
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,600
Nora?

72
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,900
I never liked that kid.

73
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:54,400
Kids his age are supposed
to be cocky, full of life.

74
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,900
You know what I mean?

75
00:12:57,100 --> 00:13:01,700
- Trouble is, Kyle thinks too much.
- We can't all be full of surprises like you.

76
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:05,300
Kyle's reliable.
She says if she marries him,

77
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:10,000
she won't have to worry about him
running off with some female half his age.

78
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:15,000
- Of course, I'm only quoting.
- That is not fair, Nora.

79
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:19,200
- OK, so Karen is 24 years old. So what?
- Fair?

80
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:22,400
Is that what you still think
life has to be, Tim? Fair?

81
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,000
Jesus Christ!
When are you gonna grow up?

82
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,500
I am trying.

83
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:31,700
I came to tell you that Karen is over.
I've broken up with her.

84
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:35,600
Poor baby. Abandoned at her tender age.

85
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:40,100
- I came hoping to talk with you.
- What are we doing, wrestling?

86
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:42,500
You're never here when I pick up Zack.

87
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,600
We have nothing more
to say to each other.

88
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,500
You wanna talk to me, talk.
Then leave me alone.

89
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:51,500
- They're at it again.
- Go put on your pants, OK?

90
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:54,300
Do you need any money?
Anything you and the kids need?

91
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:57,400
- Please, Tim, not that!
- What do you want?

92
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,800
What I have always wanted.

93
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:03,300
Somebody I can trust.
Somebody I can depend on.

94
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,500
Not you.

95
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:08,500
I do want to tell you one thing.
I figured it out.

96
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,400
I took up with Karen
because she wasn't you.

97
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,900
Even dumb me figured that one out.

98
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,900
Now I've broken it up with her
because she wasn't like you.

99
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:19,400
I can't believe anything you say, Tim.

100
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:23,900
I don't blame you.
Are you sure you want to sell the house?

101
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:29,100
The kids are settled here, and
all the work you've put in and everything.

102
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,100
OK, I'm sorry.

103
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:36,400
Too many bad memories, huh?

104
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:39,300
- And good ones.
- Good.

105
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:46,400
One thing you've gotta believe, Nora.
I never wanted to hurt you.

106
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,700
You struck out there.

107
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,600
Hey, Zack, come on, let's go!

108
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,700
- Zack.
- There's a brontosaurus in the pool.

109
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:06,900
No way. They've been extinct
for more than a million years.

110
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,900
How about a kiss?

111
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:16,200
Don't forget to tell your English teacher
the difference between "lie" and "lay".

112
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,800
- She'll flunk me for being a smart-ass.
- I doubt it.

113
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,100
Can I get a kiss? Just a friendly kiss?

114
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,500
Bye-bye, Mom. See you later.

115
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:31,100
- I'll call this afternoon. Will you be here?
- I don't think so.

116
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:35,500
- I'll leave a key under the mat.
- You take care, now.

117
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,600
You too.

118
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:42,000
You sure?

119
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,300
Sorry.

120
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:54,300
See you later.

121
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:03,700
- Hey, young fella.
- Hi.

122
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,900
- You wanna drive?
- It'd be great.

123
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:08,200
- Move over.
- All right.

124
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,500
- Go on.
- Come on, Dad. Come on.

125
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:18,800
- Let's go.
- Bye, Mom! Bye! Bye, Mommy!

126
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,500
Now what?

127
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,300
Are you gonna take a swim?

128
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:47,700
I don't get it.
Won't the cops be looking for the car?

129
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:52,100
So they will, Albert, so they will.
But not this one.

130
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:57,800
- Feast your eyes, boys.
- It's a Jaguar.

131
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,600
- We're gonna steal a Jaguar?
- Where did you get the keys?

132
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:04,500
You know who God helps,
don't you, brother?

133
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:10,700
- I never even rode in a Jaguar before.
- Hey, I told you. That's my brother.

134
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:15,100
- Mike, can I drive?
- Sure, you can drive.

135
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:20,500
You can drive that beat-up old Cougar
right into the lake.

136
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,700
Take this!

137
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:35,900
- Albert, can you whistle?
- Sure.

138
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,000
I want you to whistle so I can hear you.

139
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:43,700
I don't want you to stop unless you see
somebody comin' down the road.

140
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,000
Hey, Albert!

141
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:58,500
Move the goddamn log out of the way!

142
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,300
Geronimo!

143
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:26,800
Whoo! Mikey! Whoo! Mikey!

144
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:30,600
Mikey! Mikey!

145
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:39,100
She's good. She's real good.

146
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:44,400
You gotta hand it to her -
she's holdin' up real well.

147
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,100
And I hate playing
good cop, bad cop. It's bullshit.

148
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:50,200
I was too hard on her.

149
00:18:52,700 --> 00:18:55,300
The lady is a liar. Among other things.

150
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:58,300
- How do you get that?
- I've got a feeling.

151
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,400
Call it women's intuition.

152
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:03,000
- Bob? Bob?
- Yeah?

153
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:07,100
This is Carl Ornitz from the US Attorney's
office. He has some news for us.

154
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:10,300
Not news for the good of mankind,
I assume.

155
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:12,900
When Bosworth
was originally prosecuted,

156
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:17,100
a significant part of the government's
case was excluded from the trial

157
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:19,800
because of an inadmissible confession.

158
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,700
When he was being pursued
he broke into a liquor store.

159
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:27,800
He wanted to take the clerk with him.
The owner resisted. He was found shot.

160
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,300
A couple of weeks later,
Bosworth was arrested.

161
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:33,900
He confessed to the crime
before he was read his rights.

162
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:36,500
We think he confessed on purpose.

163
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:41,300
He was never tried for murder,
only for armed robbery.

164
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:44,900
The thing is he had a prior conviction
for burglary. The people were at home.

165
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,600
- He held 'em hostage...
- And?

166
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:50,400
- And, as usual, somebody got dead.
- Are you gonna file on her?

167
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:53,100
Better. I'm lettin' her go.

168
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:56,400
What are you talking about?
I haven't even done my affidavit yet.

169
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:59,000
Let's get a Title-3 for her phone.

170
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:03,000
Evidence won't help us with this lady,
even if we had cold proof.

171
00:20:03,100 --> 00:20:07,300
Even if that marshal recovers, she'd waltz
into court and say she was mesmerised.

172
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:10,700
"He made me do it." Temporary insanity.

173
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:15,000
Look at her. She's too smart.

174
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:18,000
I want her to be free as a kite.

175
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:21,700
I want her to go to him
because she wants him.

176
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:27,100
Then we'll take the lovebirds together.

177
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:36,800
Rich man, poor man, beggar man, thief.

178
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:42,500
I liked the one with the swimming pool.
That's pretty nice.

179
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:45,900
I think we should get the hell outta here.

180
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,600
Son of a bitch.

181
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:36,100
Yeah, my heating has gone.
My house was freezing last night.

182
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:40,100
- What's the address again?
- 1448 Whitney Drive.

183
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,300
- When can you get someone out here?
- We're really backed up.

184
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,900
We'll get someone out there
as soon as we can.

185
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,100
Is that soon as in "real soon",
or soon as in "whenever we feel like it"?

186
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,800
Do I put it on the radio or not?

187
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:57,600
Yeah. OK, just get somebody
out here, please. Thank you.

188
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,100
Calm.

189
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:12,400
Good morning. You called about
a winter cover for your pool?

190
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:16,800
What? No, I'm sorry. This house is sold.

191
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,300
Unless my husband may have called.

192
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:24,800
- Yes, it was your husband.
- But, no. He'd have told me about this.

193
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:36,700
If you scream, your children will come
home and find you in a pool of blood.

194
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,700
Please, what do you want?

195
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:44,600
Hey, there's a swimming pool
in the back. And it's heated.

196
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:50,100
- Someone left a bikini on the grass.
- That's my daughter's.

197
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:53,100
Oh, yeah? How old? Is she cute?

198
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:59,300
Keys to the station wagon?

199
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:03,800
- The keys?
- I can help you. You're scared now.

200
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:09,100
The fear will pass.
You'll feel proud of yourself.

201
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:12,300
And I'll feel proud of you.

202
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,800
The keys.

203
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,800
No one's gonna hurt you.

204
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,900
I promise.

205
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,500
OK? You're gonna learn to trust me.

206
00:24:52,300 --> 00:24:55,800
You probably can't absorb
any of this right now.

207
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,700
But you and I are gonna be friends.

208
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:06,900
Would you like to go upstairs
and put something else on?

209
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:01,600
Albert! What are you doing up there?

210
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:18,700
Albert, were you in Nora's bedroom?

211
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:22,300
You are never to enter that bedroom
without Nora's permission.

212
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:25,100
I parked the Jag in the garage.

213
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:28,100
Let's just take the car and go.
I don't like it here.

214
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,300
Then you leave.

215
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:35,800
You're only here because when I was
in prison, my brother needed your help.

216
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:40,000
I want you to go through the house.
Look for money and jewellery.

217
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:44,100
Nora, sit down. Sit down.
I wanna reassure you.

218
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:51,700
- You have a daughter, May?
- How did you know her name?

219
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:56,600
I was going through
your husband's letters, and... She's 15.

220
00:26:56,800 --> 00:27:00,300
- Then there's the younger child.
- Zack, he's...

221
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:05,000
He's eight? They come home
from school around what time?

222
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:11,200
Nora, don't make me resent the kids
before I even meet them.

223
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:13,700
Zack gets dropped off around three.

224
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:16,500
- By a carpool?
- Yes.

225
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:19,800
Does the parent come to the door?

226
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:23,800
No. Picking the children up is hectic
enough without dropping them off.

227
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,900
Give me a break, lady.

228
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:29,900
Do you think you could
speak on the telephone without crying?

229
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:33,000
If you can, we can be outta here
a hell of a lot faster.

230
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:37,900
- Yes, anything.
- You're a strong woman, Nora.

231
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:42,100
- Smart men love strong women.
- What if they tap Nancy's phone?

232
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:44,900
She's a victim. They'd never suspect her.

233
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,100
I'm a very fair man, Nora.

234
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:51,400
I'd never hurt anyone
unless they were trying to hurt me.

235
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:53,600
I swear it.

236
00:27:53,700 --> 00:27:55,900
Here's what I want you to say:

237
00:27:56,000 --> 00:28:00,700
