605
01:01:29,000 --> 01:01:31,000
Get the door.

606
01:02:20,200 --> 01:02:24,400
Got only one thing for you
to think about out there.

607
01:02:24,500 --> 01:02:30,100
Any red-light show,
any sirens, they get it first.

608
01:02:30,300 --> 01:02:33,300
Not you, them. You think about that.

609
01:02:35,600 --> 01:02:37,500
Good morning, sir.

610
01:02:48,000 --> 01:02:51,100
- Sorry.
- She was next.

611
01:02:56,200 --> 01:02:58,500
We usually require your wife's signature.

612
01:02:58,600 --> 01:03:01,600
My wife's not well.
I've been banking here for 14 years.

613
01:03:01,800 --> 01:03:05,900
I opened the account myself
and I want to close it out myself.

614
01:03:06,000 --> 01:03:09,800
- I'll have to talk to Mr Nelson.
- Is he in? Good.

615
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:21,100
Mr Cornell? You know there's a penalty
for cashing these certificates out?

616
01:03:21,200 --> 01:03:24,200
I know that. But it's unavoidable, you see.

617
01:03:24,400 --> 01:03:27,600
I just need the cash. It's an emergency.

618
01:03:30,100 --> 01:03:34,400
If you'll sign right there,
I'll cash you out, Mr Cornell.

619
01:03:34,500 --> 01:03:38,000
- Cashiers' cheque?
- No, cash, please.

620
01:03:38,100 --> 01:03:40,100
Cash.

621
01:03:42,600 --> 01:03:44,600
And one more, please.

622
01:03:47,100 --> 01:03:51,100
- Very kind of you. Thank you.
- It'll be a moment.

623
01:04:05,500 --> 01:04:08,300
Here you are, Mr Cornell.
But please count it.

624
01:04:08,500 --> 01:04:10,900
I'm sure it's OK. Thanks.

625
01:04:11,000 --> 01:04:12,900
Thanks a lot.

626
01:04:14,400 --> 01:04:16,300
Who's next, please?

627
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:37,700
The FBI announced today it will not
file charges against Nancy Breyers

628
01:06:37,800 --> 01:06:41,300
