- I can hear your knees.

727
01:16:52,400 --> 01:16:56,500
You do this, no charges will be brought.
You can't turn your back now.

728
01:16:56,700 --> 01:17:00,600
- If you do, we're gonna take casualties.
- I know. I know.

729
01:17:00,800 --> 01:17:03,700
You think she'll think straight
when she's with Bosworth?

730
01:17:03,800 --> 01:17:06,100
She's got her brains between her legs.

731
01:17:06,300 --> 01:17:09,500
I can be inside that house in one minute.
Flashbangs at the door.

732
01:17:09,600 --> 01:17:13,600
- We make a three-point entry, it's all over.
- We're givin' that family a chance.

733
01:17:13,800 --> 01:17:17,500
The way they played along, maybe
they don't have any chance coming.

734
01:17:17,600 --> 01:17:19,500
You don't give a damn, do you?

735
01:17:19,600 --> 01:17:22,700
If it goes sideways,
we'll waste the whole neighbourhood.

736
01:17:38,200 --> 01:17:41,700
Don't forget to smile when you see him.

737
01:17:42,800 --> 01:17:46,000
He might want me to...

738
01:17:46,400 --> 01:17:49,300
Well, smile when you do that too.

739
01:17:49,400 --> 01:17:51,500
Oh, God, I can't.

740
01:17:51,700 --> 01:17:53,600
You can.

741
01:17:55,400 --> 01:17:58,500
- I'm not ready to die.
- Then you make sure

742
01:17:58,600 --> 01:18:01,100
you do just what I told you.

743
01:18:02,600 --> 01:18:05,200
What happens when we come outside?

744
01:18:05,300 --> 01:18:09,700
What if he realises what I'm doing to him?

745
01:18:09,900 --> 01:18:13,200
I want a gun, or I won't go in. I won't.

746
01:18:31,800 --> 01:18:34,200
I just put my ass on the line.

747
01:18:34,400 --> 01:18:37,500
Now you get outta here.
My earrings are killing me.

748
01:18:37,700 --> 01:18:39,600
I'm in a real bad mood.

749
01:18:39,800 --> 01:18:41,700
You be careful.

750
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:58,100
I'm passing command to you.

751
01:18:58,200 --> 01:19:02,600
If you fuck this up, you'll leave
your badge in a manila envelope.

752
01:19:02,700 --> 01:19:04,800
'Cause I don't want to see you
when I get back.

753
01:19:04,900 --> 01:19:07,000
I'm goin' to the observation point.

754
01:19:55,400 --> 01:19:57,800
Subject is on the scene.

755
01:20:32,200 --> 01:20:36,200
I know that they tried
to get you to betray me.

756
01:21:01,300 --> 01:21:03,400
Let me introduce you to the Cornells.

757
01:21:03,500 --> 01:21:06,800
I got this wacko in my sights.
I think I can take him.

758
01:21:06,900 --> 01:21:09,400
That's Zack, and May.

759
01:21:09,600 --> 01:21:13,100
And Nora. This is
the greatest woman in the world.

760
01:21:13,200 --> 01:21:17,400
My God, what are you doing?
You must be insane.

761
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:20,700
- You shut up!
- Zack, go upstairs, now.

762
01:21:25,600 --> 01:21:29,300
Nancy, I have somethin' that I wanna...

763
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:37,600
I wanna give to you. It's gonna keep us
together for the rest of our lives.

764
01:21:37,800 --> 01:21:40,500
- I can't take that.
- This used to be Nora's.

765
01:21:43,900 --> 01:21:46,900
- What's going on?
- Turn around.

766
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:51,900
- I gotta get through to see somebody.
- We got a problem with the traffic.

767
01:21:53,000 --> 01:21:54,900
Hey!

768
01:22:04,500 --> 01:22:07,900
Jesus Christ! We've got company.

769
01:22:08,000 --> 01:22:10,100
Goddamn son of a bitch.

770
01:22:22,700 --> 01:22:25,400
It's too late. See what he does.

771
01:22:26,400 --> 01:22:28,700
- May!
- Who's that?

772
01:22:28,900 --> 01:22:30,900
It's May's boyfriend.

773
01:22:31,000 --> 01:22:34,100
Come on, May, open up.

774
01:22:42,600 --> 01:22:45,100
Hi, Kyle. How you doin', kid?

775
01:22:47,400 --> 01:22:50,600
I'm sorry to stop by so late, but I...

776
01:22:50,800 --> 01:22:57,500
May and I had a fight, and if she could go
for a ride with me, I'd really appreciate it.

777
01:22:58,300 --> 01:23:01,600
She may still be angry, pal. I'll ask her.

778
01:23:03,400 --> 01:23:06,500
- I'll wait for her here.
- OK, you bet.

779
01:23:15,400 --> 01:23:19,000
He wants to take May for a ride.
He won't leave without her.

780
01:23:19,200 --> 01:23:23,000
- That's one less we gotta worry about.
- Then you call her.

781
01:23:23,100 --> 01:23:24,900
May!

782
01:23:25,900 --> 01:23:27,900
May, come down, please.

783
01:23:35,600 --> 01:23:38,400
May, Kyle's outside.

784
01:23:39,100 --> 01:23:43,600
He wants to make it up with you.
Now, you have to go. Now.

785
01:23:46,200 --> 01:23:48,500
Go on with him.

786
01:23:48,600 --> 01:23:51,200
I'm not leaving
unless my mom stays here.

787
01:23:51,300 --> 01:23:53,800
Nora's comin' with me.

788
01:23:54,000 --> 01:23:56,900
- What for?
- So you don't call the cops when we go.

789
01:23:57,000 --> 01:24:00,100
Bosworth, you are so close.
Don't blow it.

790
01:24:00,300 --> 01:24:03,200
If she doesn't go,
Kyle will make a scene. I know it.

791
01:24:03,300 --> 01:24:05,900
Let her go, Mike, please.

792
01:24:06,100 --> 01:24:12,300
You and I have a date with destiny, Tim.
You'll be comin' with me, after all.

793
01:24:12,400 --> 01:24:16,000
I could trust Nora
more than I could trust you.

794
01:24:17,700 --> 01:24:19,600
Dad, what about you?

795
01:24:20,500 --> 01:24:23,200
We're gonna win if you do as he says.

796
01:24:23,300 --> 01:24:25,600
I love you, Daddy.

797
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:29,400
I love you.

798
01:24:32,100 --> 01:24:33,700
Go.

799
01:24:34,800 --> 01:24:36,800
OK, OK.

800
01:24:38,200 --> 01:24:41,100
You go with your boyfriend, May.

801
01:24:41,300 --> 01:24:43,900
You go far away.

802
01:24:44,400 --> 01:24:47,400
Otherwise I'm gonna kill your daddy.

803
01:24:57,200 --> 01:24:59,800
- Are you OK?
- I'm fine.

804
01:24:59,900 --> 01:25:04,300
I don't know what's goin' on,
but let's get outta here.

805
01:25:15,300 --> 01:25:18,100
Right. You move it. You get the car.

806
01:25:46,000 --> 01:25:52,800
Mr Cornell, I'm Special Agent Brenda
Chandler, FBl. We're here to help you.

807
01:25:53,000 --> 01:25:55,900
You can't do that.
You'll get my family killed.

808
01:25:56,000 --> 01:25:58,600
We're gonna let them drive away.

809
01:25:58,800 --> 01:26:02,200
No, I'm going with them.
Bosworth and his brother and the girl.

810
01:26:02,400 --> 01:26:04,500
- You're hurt.
- No, I'm not.

811
01:26:06,300 --> 01:26:08,700
I'm OK.

812
01:26:12,300 --> 01:26:17,500
Don't take long in there.
He's gonna go suicidal any minute now.

813
01:26:27,600 --> 01:26:30,800
- Why are you doin' that?
- A wild idea. You have to trust me.

814
01:26:30,900 --> 01:26:33,100
Mr Cornell.

815
01:26:33,200 --> 01:26:38,100
If we have to go tactical,
we're gonna take casualties.

816
01:26:38,200 --> 01:26:40,400
It's one more chance I'll have to take.

817
01:26:45,300 --> 01:26:49,600
- How come I didn't hear the car start?
- No key.

818
01:26:49,700 --> 01:26:51,700
Put your arms up.

819
01:26:54,700 --> 01:26:57,300
What is this? Huh? What's this?

820
01:26:57,400 --> 01:27:01,500
- Huh? What the fuck is this?
- I found it on the seat of her car.

821
01:27:01,600 --> 01:27:03,800
I was... I was scared.

822
01:27:04,000 --> 01:27:06,400
All right. You get goin' now.

823
01:27:07,900 --> 01:27:10,700
I wanna say goodbye to Zack.

824
01:27:15,700 --> 01:27:19,400
Hey, Daddy.
There's people with guns outside.

825
01:27:19,500 --> 01:27:22,500
- I saw them. I'm scared.
- Shh.

826
01:27:22,600 --> 01:27:24,500
You must be quiet.

827
01:27:24,700 --> 01:27:27,900
You can't do this to me.
You've got to speak quietly.

828
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:32,100
- Are they gonna shoot us?
- No, no. They're here to help us.

829
01:27:32,200 --> 01:27:35,300
I know you're scared.
But we mustn't let the men know.

830
01:27:49,900 --> 01:27:51,800
OK, I'll be back soon.

831
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:55,900
- Tim.
- What?

832
01:27:56,000 --> 01:27:58,300
Tim,

833
01:27:58,400 --> 01:28:01,700
there's so many things I want to tell you.

834
01:28:01,800 --> 01:28:05,900
- And I don't have time to tell you.
- I know. Me too.

835
01:28:18,300 --> 01:28:23,300
This place is a tomb.
You two get out first. Get in the back.

836
01:28:23,500 --> 01:28:26,500
Nancy, start the engine.
Don't turn on the lights.

837
01:28:54,100 --> 01:28:57,500
- Shit.
- Nancy, what's wrong?

838
01:28:57,600 --> 01:28:59,900
No!

839
01:29:00,700 --> 01:29:02,800
Hold it! Hold it!

840
01:29:05,400 --> 01:29:07,500
Hold it, Bosworth!

841
01:29:11,500 --> 01:29:14,100
- Where are you hit?
- In the ego!

842
01:29:14,200 --> 01:29:16,800
Get me a bullhorn!

843
01:29:41,100 --> 01:29:43,600
- What if they shoot Daddy?
- They won't.

844
01:29:43,700 --> 01:29:46,900
- You betrayed me!
- Michael, no!

845
01:29:47,000 --> 01:29:49,600
Michael, please.

846
01:29:49,700 --> 01:29:52,200
I did all this for you!

847
01:29:54,300 --> 01:29:57,000
You shut up. Shut up. This ain't over.

848
01:29:59,200 --> 01:30:01,200
You watch him.

849
01:30:05,200 --> 01:30:11,400
This is Michael Bosworth speaking.
So before you start with your bullshit,

850
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:18,100
I want a car here to take three,
no, four people to the airport.

851
01:30:18,200 --> 01:30:22,600
- I want a plane with five hours of fuel.
- I'll see what I can do on that.

852
01:30:22,700 --> 01:30:27,800
Don't you start lying to me.
I know who's in charge out there.

853
01:30:28,000 --> 01:30:34,300
You listen to me. I want all your people
out of there in ten minutes,

854
01:30:34,400 --> 01:30:36,400
or I'll kill the whole family.

855
01:30:37,600 --> 01:30:40,700
- We can't negotiate him out.
- There are four hostages.

856
01:30:40,800 --> 01:30:44,100
- Bosworth needs killing.
- We don't violate the rules

857
01:30:44,200 --> 01:30:46,400
until they don't work.

858
01:30:46,500 --> 01:30:51,100
Everyone's alive. So far,
this is still a potential win.

859
01:30:51,300 --> 01:30:55,100
Someone bring a four-door car
to the house. Now.

860
01:30:55,400 --> 01:30:57,600
Be careful, Zack. Be careful, honey.

861
01:30:57,700 --> 01:31:00,800
It's OK, Mommy, don't worry.

862
01:31:01,000 --> 01:31:03,300
- Be careful!
- I love you. You'll be OK.

863
01:31:03,400 --> 01:31:06,100
Drop him!

864
01:31:09,400 --> 01:31:12,600
They're gonna get us outta here yet!

865
01:31:15,200 --> 01:31:17,400
Wally!

866
01:31:17,500 --> 01:31:19,500
- Give me the gun.
- Nora!

867
01:31:22,400 --> 01:31:25,500
- Nora!
- You're dying, Wally.

868
01:31:25,600 --> 01:31:29,600
- You're dying. You're not going anywhere.
- Nora!

869
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:38,400
Give me the gun. Give me the gun!

870
01:31:47,400 --> 01:31:50,500
Goddammit! Get over here!

871
01:31:51,400 --> 01:31:53,300
- Get over here!
- No!

872
01:31:55,500 --> 01:31:57,700
Wally!

873
01:32:00,400 --> 01:32:02,300
Oh, God.

874
01:32:16,500 --> 01:32:19,700
I have decided
I love your family too much.

875
01:32:19,800 --> 01:32:24,500
You're all coming with me.
The more the merrier, right?

876
01:32:24,700 --> 01:32:28,700
You're through, Bosworth. It's over.

877
01:32:28,800 --> 01:32:31,600
You stay right there
or you're going to kill your wife.

878
01:32:31,800 --> 01:32:34,400
- Tim!
- It's OK, Nora.

879
01:32:35,100 --> 01:32:38,500
- Tim.
- I'm still in control, Timmy.

880
01:32:38,600 --> 01:32:42,300
- Tim!
- Nothing can happen to you, Nora.

881
01:32:42,400 --> 01:32:46,100
If you never trusted me before,
you have to trust me now.

882
01:32:46,200 --> 01:32:50,100
I'll blow her brains right across the room.

883
01:32:50,200 --> 01:32:56,500
You know what size hole this calibre
bullet makes when it exits the other side?

884
01:32:57,700 --> 01:32:59,700
He can't hurt you, Nora.

885
01:32:59,800 --> 01:33:01,900
He can't hurt you, honey.

886
01:33:43,300 --> 01:33:46,500
Your car is waiting, Bosworth.

887
01:34:20,200 --> 01:34:22,500
Do not move!

888
01:34:22,600 --> 01:34:25,200
Stay down!

889
01:34:48,900 --> 01:34:52,600
Do not move! We'll come to you!

890
01:35:16,500 --> 01:35:18,300
Nancy!

891
01:35:51,700 --> 01:35:54,500
Blade, get her out of here, will ya?